\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {The edit task: scoring methodology and qualitative examples.} \emph  {Left:} the BenchCAD-Edit scoring pipeline --- given an original program, a natural-language instruction, and a model edit, we score \emph  {target success} (does the requested feature change?) and \emph  {non-target preservation} (do unrelated features remain unchanged?) independently, with full Pass@1 requiring both. \emph  {Right:} three representative edit pairs (dimensional, additive, subtractive, multi-step), each showing the original part, the instruction, the model edit, and the target --- with cases of clean success, target-success-only Edit Leakage (the requested change applied but unrelated features corrupted), and multi-step collapse where the parametric dependency is missed. \emph  {[Figure to be composed; placeholder.]}}}{16}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
